String rjust() The string rjust() method returns a new string of given length after
substituting a given character in left side of original string.





Syntax:

string.rjust(length, fillchar)







Parameters:

length: length of the modified string. If length is less than or equal to the length of the
        original string then original string is returned.

fillchar: (optional) characters which needs to be padded. If itâ€™s not provided, space is
          taken as a default argument.







Returns:

Returns a new string of given length after substituting a given character in left side of
original string.